Privacy Policy for tinycore-api

Effective Date: 2024-09-11

"tinycore-api" is developed to integrate with smart sensors and notify users about the status of a space (e.g., whether the space is open or closed). We take your privacy seriously and are committed to protecting the personal data of all users.
Information We Collect

When you use tinycore-api, we may collect the following information:

    Account Information: We collect your Amazon user ID and profile information when you link your Amazon account with our skill through account linking.
    Sensor Data: We collect and process information from your smart devices (such as door sensors or light sensors) to determine the status of the space (e.g., whether it’s open or closed).

We do not collect personally identifiable information unless necessary for the functionality of the skill.
How We Use Your Information

We use the collected data to:

    Provide Core Skill Functionality: Sensor data is used to notify you about the status of the space, whether it's open or closed.
    Account Linking: Your Amazon account information is used to enable account linking, so you can control your smart devices with Alexa and receive space status updates.

How We Store and Protect Your Information

We store your data securely using Amazon Web Services (AWS), which provides industry-standard security measures. We take all necessary steps to protect your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

How We Share Your Information

We do not share your personal data with third parties except as necessary to operate the skill. We may share your data with:

    Third-Party Services: If required for functionality, such as API services for processing space status updates.

We do not sell, rent, or lease your data to any other parties.

Your Rights and Control Over Your Data

You have the right to:

    Access the Data We Collect: You can request to view the data we have collected.
    Request Data Deletion: You can request the deletion of your data by contacting us at the email provided below.
    Revoke Permissions: You can unlink your Amazon account from the skill at any time through the Alexa app.

Data Retention

We retain your data only as long as necessary to provide the skill’s services. If you unlink the skill or request deletion, we will remove all collected data within a reasonable time.
Third-Party Services

Our skill may interact with third-party services (e.g., Space API) to update the status of a space. These services may have their own privacy policies governing their use of your information.
Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will notify you by updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this page.
Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

tinycore.lab
tinycore.lab@autistici.org
